            "image": "shopify://shop_images/kiku2.png",
            "image_width": 50,
            "image_border_radius": 0,
            "content_gap": 10,
            "heading": "About the material ",
            "heading_size": 32,
            "heading_color": "#000000",
            "text": "<p>For example, our ingredients are organically grown fresh konnyaku yams, which are grown over two to three years in the fertile soil of the mountains of Fuchu City, Hiroshima Prefecture, surrounded by nature . We don't use any artificial coagulants, but instead solidify the yams with wood ash and seashells. We spare no effort or time in allowing the yams to mature slowly.<br/>While these are the polar opposite of efficiency and low cost, Kikumatsu believes they are essential conditions for konnyaku to retain its inherent flavor and be a safe food. This sentiment extends not only to konnyaku itself, but also to amagusa, the main ingredient in tokoroten. We preserve the original texture, mouthfeel, and flavor of konnyaku, and, based on that foundation, we are constantly striving to create new interpretations and experiments, striving to further \"deliciousness\" so that everyone can enjoy delicious konnyaku dishes with peace of mind. To achieve this, there are many hurdles to overcome, such as further learning, further efforts, and improvement of skills, but with pride and ambition as a konnyaku shop, and with the \"delicious smiles\" of our customers as our guide, we will continue to work hard as a fourth-generation konnyaku shop, as we have done until now and will continue to do so in the future.</p>",
