    "rich_text_Hj8j6C": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_cXaRr6": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Kikumatsu's Thoughts",
            "heading_tag": "h2"
          }
        },
        "richtext_anwX7X": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Kikumatsu regularly visits the konnyaku fields in Hiroshima Prefecture.<br/>We drive up the mountain so much that the sky feels closer, and before we know it, we arrive at a village surrounded by greenery on all sides.<br/>We will check to see that the organically grown konnyaku potatoes are growing vigorously in the terraced fields in the mountains.</p><p>In order to make delicious and safe konnyaku that everyone can enjoy, it is essential that the ingredients are healthy.<br/>This is Kikumatsu's philosophy of \"reliable manufacturing,\" which is common not only to konnyaku potatoes but also to wood ash, water, and other materials.</p><p>The smile of the konnyaku farmer who said, \"The konnyaku is growing well again this year!\" was the same as Kikumatsu's smile after he received the baton.<br/>It is with this dream that we face konnyaku every day, hoping to bring even more smiles to our customers' dinner tables.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        }
      },
